Lead Buyer
-
Date Posted: 2014/04/30 06:00:50
Ref. JB3045695
Job Description
A leading international player in marine services, BOURBON offers to the most demanding oil & gas clients worldwide a full line of innovative, safe, high performance and new generation vessels and an expanded offer of offshore oil & gas services. Bourbon Sourcing recruits a Lead Buyer Duties & Responsibilities   - Define and propose annual policy on its portfolio (Suppliers market share, new supplier introduction).- Negotiate frame agreement. - Input price list in the system and / or Open Blanket Order. - Purchasing responsibility: Purchase for Repairrr centre / onshore stock. Validate PO's.- Manage suppliers' relationship. - Source new suppliers in link with life-cycle organization.       Line reporting and functional linkage You report directly to the Managing Director of Bourbon Sourcing.
Skills
Key skills - Personal organization- Actian plan settling- Mastery of problem solving techniques  Behavior - Autonomous - Rigour - Good relationship and communication skills  Experience At least 5 years experience in a similar position in the Industrial, Oil and Gas and / or Marine  field.Experience with quotations in:- Shipyard repairs, Ship agency; or - Consumables, Catering.  Languages English is mandatory  Computer knowledge Proficient in MS Office, ORACLE database  Education Engineering degree  Contract Unlimited contract based in Dubai to be filled immediately.
